## Description {#details}

This file implements a register stacking pass.

This pass reorders instructions to put register uses and defs in an order such that they form single-use expression trees. Registers fitting this form are then marked as &quot;stackified&quot;, meaning references to them are replaced by &quot;push&quot; and &quot;pop&quot; from the value stack.

This is primarily a code size optimization, since temporary values on the value stack don&#39;t need to be named.

### moveAndTeeForMultiUse() {#ad7ed3a1e19bd5b3c4ea5a74413371900}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static MachineInstr &#42; moveAndTeeForMultiUse (unsigned Reg, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machineoperand">MachineOperand</a> &amp; Op, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machineinstr">MachineInstr</a> &#42; Def, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machinebasicblock">MachineBasicBlock</a> &amp; MBB, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machineinstr">MachineInstr</a> &#42; Insert, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/liveintervals">LiveIntervals</a> &amp; LIS, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/webassemblyfunctioninfo">WebAssemblyFunctionInfo</a> &amp; MFI, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machineregisterinfo">MachineRegisterInfo</a> &amp; MRI, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/webassemblyinstrinfo">WebAssemblyInstrInfo</a> &#42; TII)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
A multiple-use def in the same block with no intervening memory or register dependencies; move the def down, nest it with the current instruction, and insert a tee to satisfy the rest of the uses.

As an illustration, rewrite this:

Reg = INST ... // Def INST ..., Reg, ... // Insert INST ..., Reg, ... INST ..., Reg, ...

to this:

DefReg = INST ... // Def (to become the new Insert) TeeReg, Reg = TEE&#95;... DefReg INST ..., TeeReg, ... // Insert INST ..., Reg, ... INST ..., Reg, ...

with DefReg and TeeReg stackified. This eliminates a local.get from the resulting code.

Definition at line <a href="#l00633">633</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/webassembly/webassemblyregstackify-cpp">WebAssemblyRegStackify.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

<Link id="l00613" /><CodeLine lineNumber="613"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// A multiple-use def in the same block with no intervening memory or register</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00614" /><CodeLine lineNumber="614"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// dependencies; move the def down, nest it with the current instruction, and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00615" /><CodeLine lineNumber="615"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// insert a tee to satisfy the rest of the uses. As an illustration, rewrite</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00616" /><CodeLine lineNumber="616"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// this:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00617" /><CodeLine lineNumber="617"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00618" /><CodeLine lineNumber="618"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    Reg = INST ...        // Def</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00619" /><CodeLine lineNumber="619"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    INST ..., Reg, ...    // Insert</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00620" /><CodeLine lineNumber="620"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    INST ..., Reg, ...</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00621" /><CodeLine lineNumber="621"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    INST ..., Reg, ...</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00622" /><CodeLine lineNumber="622"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00623" /><CodeLine lineNumber="623"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// to this:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00624" /><CodeLine lineNumber="624"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00625" /><CodeLine lineNumber="625"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    DefReg = INST ...     // Def (to become the new Insert)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00626" /><CodeLine lineNumber="626"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    TeeReg, Reg = TEE&#95;... DefReg</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00627" /><CodeLine lineNumber="627"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    INST ..., TeeReg, ... // Insert</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00628" /><CodeLine lineNumber="628"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    INST ..., Reg, ...</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00629" /><CodeLine lineNumber="629"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    INST ..., Reg, ...</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00630" /><CodeLine lineNumber="630"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00631" /><CodeLine lineNumber="631"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// with DefReg and TeeReg stackified. This eliminates a local.get from the</span></CodeLine>
